## PHASE 1: SCHEMA DISCOVERY AND COLUMN PROFILING
================================================================================

Complete this phase fully before proceeding to Phase 2.

### Step 1.1 — Fetch Schema

run_sql("""
  SELECT table_name, column_name, data_type,
         character_maximum_length, numeric_precision, numeric_scale
  FROM information_schema.columns
  WHERE table_name IN ('PRODUCT_DIM', 'MSD_CURRENT')
  ORDER BY table_name, ordinal_position
""")

### Step 1.2 — Profile Every Column

For each column in both tables:

run_sql("""
  SELECT
    '{TABLE}'                                                 AS table_name,
    '{COL}'                                                   AS column_name,
    COUNT(*)                                                  AS total_rows,
    COUNT("{COL}")                                            AS non_null_count,
    ROUND(100.0*(COUNT(*)-COUNT("{COL}"))/NULLIF(COUNT(*),0),2) AS null_pct,
    COUNT(DISTINCT "{COL}")                                   AS distinct_count,
    MIN(LENGTH(TRIM(CAST("{COL}" AS VARCHAR))))               AS min_len,
    MAX(LENGTH(TRIM(CAST("{COL}" AS VARCHAR))))               AS max_len,
    MIN(CAST("{COL}" AS VARCHAR))                             AS val_min,
    MAX(CAST("{COL}" AS VARCHAR))                             AS val_max,
    ARRAY_AGG(DISTINCT CAST("{COL}" AS VARCHAR))
      WITHIN GROUP (ORDER BY CAST("{COL}" AS VARCHAR))
      LIMIT 15                                                AS sample_values
  FROM {TABLE}
""")

Store results as: column_profiles[table][column]

### Step 1.3 — Assign Value Pattern

Assign exactly one pattern label per column using this decision tree in order:

  IF data_type = DATE or TIMESTAMP               → ISO_DATE

  IF data_type is numeric AND distinct_count <= 2 → BOOLEAN_NUMERIC

  IF data_type is numeric:
    val range 0–1                                → RATE_DECIMAL_0TO1
    val range 0–20, non-integer                  → RATE_DECIMAL_PCT
    val range 0–2000, integers only              → RATE_BASISPTS
    val_min > 100,000                            → AMOUNT_ACTUAL
    val range 100–10,000,000 (ambiguous scale)   → AMOUNT_SCALE_AMBIGUOUS
    otherwise                                    → NUMERIC_GENERIC

  IF data_type is string/text:

    distinct_count <= 2
    AND values ⊆ {Y,N,YES,NO,T,F,TRUE,FALSE,1,0}  → BOOLEAN_YN

    min_len = max_len = 9, alphanumeric only       → run check:
      SELECT COUNT(*) WHERE NOT REGEXP_LIKE(col,'^[A-Z0-9]{9}$')
      if failures < 1%                             → CUSIP_9CHAR

    min_len = max_len = 8, all digits              → run check:
      SELECT COUNT(*) WHERE TRY_TO_DATE(col,'YYYYMMDD') IS NULL
        AND col NOT IN ('00000000','99999999')
      if failures < 5%                             → DATE_STRING_YYYYMMDD

    min_len = max_len = 8 AND TRY_TO_DATE fails for YYYYMMDD
      AND TRY_TO_DATE(col,'MMDDYYYY') succeeds > 90% → DATE_STRING_MMDDYYYY

    5-char all-digit, last 3 digits 001–366        → DATE_JULIAN_YYDDD

    7-char all-digit, last 3 digits 001–366        → DATE_JULIAN_YYYYDDD

    distinct_count <= 5 AND max_len <= 3           → CODE_TINY
    distinct_count <= 25 AND max_len <= 5          → CODE_SMALL
    distinct_count <= 25 AND max_len <= 15         → CODE_MEDIUM

    values match known rating notation
    (AAA,AA+,Aa1,BBB-,NR,WR etc.)                 → RATING_STRING

    values are 2-char alpha AND ⊆ US state set     → STATE_ALPHA
    values are 2-digit numeric AND ⊆ FIPS set      → FIPS_STATE_CODE
    values are 2-digit zero-padded numeric,
    distinct_count <= 20                           → CODE_NUMERIC_PADDED

    distinct_count > 1000 OR max_len > 50          → FREE_TEXT

    otherwise                                      → UNKNOWN

### Step 1.4 — Detect Sentinel Values

For each string/text column, check for values that represent missing data
rather than actual content:

run_sql("""
  SELECT CAST("{COL}" AS VARCHAR) AS raw_val, COUNT(*) AS freq
  FROM {TABLE}
  WHERE "{COL}" IS NOT NULL
  GROUP BY 1
  HAVING raw_val IN (
    ' ','  ','   ','        ',
    'N/A','NA','NONE','NOT AVAIL','UNKN','UNK','?',
    '0','0.00','00000000','99999999','9999','-1',
    'NR','N/R','WR','WD','--'
  )
  ORDER BY freq DESC
""")

Store as: column_profiles[table][column].sentinels

