## PHASE 2: MAPPING DISCOVERY
================================================================================

Run after Phase 1 is complete for both tables.

### Step 2.1 — Build Candidate Column Pairs

For every column in MSD_CURRENT find candidates in PRODUCT_DIM using four signals:

SIGNAL A — PATTERN FAMILY COMPATIBILITY
  Use this matrix (✓ = compatible, ~ = possible with transformation):

  Legacy Pattern           Compatible Modern Pattern(s)
  ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
  DATE_STRING_YYYYMMDD   → ISO_DATE                         (✓)
  DATE_STRING_MMDDYYYY   → ISO_DATE                         (✓)
  DATE_JULIAN_YYDDD      → ISO_DATE                         (✓)
  DATE_JULIAN_YYYYDDD    → ISO_DATE                         (✓)
  RATE_BASISPTS          → RATE_DECIMAL_PCT, RATE_DECIMAL_0TO1  (✓)
  RATE_DECIMAL_PCT       → RATE_DECIMAL_0TO1                (~)
  AMOUNT_SCALE_AMBIGUOUS → AMOUNT_ACTUAL                    (✓)
  AMOUNT_ACTUAL          → AMOUNT_ACTUAL                    (✓)
  CODE_TINY              → CODE_TINY, FREE_TEXT             (✓)
  CODE_SMALL             → CODE_SMALL, CODE_MEDIUM, FREE_TEXT  (✓)
  CODE_NUMERIC_PADDED    → CODE_SMALL, FREE_TEXT            (✓)
  FIPS_STATE_CODE        → STATE_ALPHA                      (✓)
  BOOLEAN_YN             → BOOLEAN_YN, BOOLEAN_NUMERIC      (✓)
  RATING_STRING          → RATING_STRING                    (✓)
  CUSIP_9CHAR            → CUSIP_9CHAR                      (✓)
  FREE_TEXT              → FREE_TEXT                        (✓)
  NUMERIC_GENERIC        → NUMERIC_GENERIC, AMOUNT_ACTUAL   (~)
  UNKNOWN                → do not auto-map, escalate

SIGNAL B — NAME TOKEN SIMILARITY
  Tokenize column names:
    1. Split on underscore
    2. Strip known suffixes: CD, NO, NM, DT, RT, AMT, IND, FLG, TYP,
       PCT, NBR, VAL, CNV, FREQ, STS, NUM, PCD, CDE
    3. Compute Jaccard similarity on remaining token sets:
       similarity = |token_intersection| / |token_union|
  Threshold: similarity > 0.4 → add as candidate

SIGNAL C — CARDINALITY ALIGNMENT
  IF |distinct_count_legacy - distinct_count_modern| /
     MAX(distinct_count_legacy, distinct_count_modern) < 0.3:
  → cardinality_aligned = TRUE

SIGNAL D — VALUE VOCABULARY OVERLAP
  For CODE_* pattern columns, sample 500 matched rows (join on CUSIP + DWR_NO).
  Build co-occurrence: for each legacy value, which modern values appear?
  vocabulary_coverage = rows where legacy value maps to exactly one modern value
                        / total non-null rows
  vocabulary_coverage > 0.80 → strong candidate evidence

### Step 2.2 — Score Candidates

  score = 0
  pattern_compatible:           +40
  token_similarity > 0.6:       +30
  token_similarity 0.4–0.6:     +15
  cardinality_aligned:          +15
  vocabulary_coverage > 0.80:   +15

  HIGH   (score ≥ 80): proceed to Phase 3
  MEDIUM (score 50–79): proceed, flag MAPPING_NEEDS_REVIEW
  LOW    (score 30–49): do not compare, escalate to human
  NONE   (score < 30):  no mapping found

### Step 2.3 — Conflict Resolution

  Multiple PRODUCT_DIM candidates at HIGH/MEDIUM → pick highest score,
    flag MAPPING_AMBIGUOUS, list all candidates

  No candidate for MSD column   → DEPRECATED_FIELD
  No candidate for PD column    → NEW_FIELD
  UNKNOWN pattern on either side → NEEDS_HUMAN, do not auto-map

### Step 2.4 — Transformation Discovery

For each HIGH or MEDIUM mapped pair, discover the transformation using samples.

DATE FORMAT DETECTION:
  run_sql("""
    SELECT
      SUM(CASE WHEN TRY_TO_DATE(CAST("{COL}" AS VARCHAR),'YYYYMMDD') IS NOT NULL
               THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)*100.0/COUNT(*) AS pct_yyyymmdd,
      SUM(CASE WHEN TRY_TO_DATE(CAST("{COL}" AS VARCHAR),'MMDDYYYY') IS NOT NULL
               THEN 1 ELSE 0 END)*100.0/COUNT(*) AS pct_mmddyyyy
    FROM {TABLE} WHERE "{COL}" IS NOT NULL
      AND CAST("{COL}" AS VARCHAR) NOT IN ('00000000','99999999')
  """)
  Format with > 90% parse rate = discovered format.
  If no format exceeds 90% → flag DATE_FORMAT_UNKNOWN, escalate.

NUMERIC SCALE DETECTION:
  run_sql("""
    SELECT
      PERCENTILE_CONT(0.5) WITHIN GROUP
        (ORDER BY CAST(p.{PD_COL} AS FLOAT)
               / NULLIF(CAST(m.{MSD_COL} AS FLOAT),0)) AS median_ratio,
      STDDEV(CAST(p.{PD_COL} AS FLOAT)
           / NULLIF(CAST(m.{MSD_COL} AS FLOAT),0))     AS ratio_stddev
    FROM PRODUCT_DIM p
    JOIN MSD_CURRENT m
      ON TRIM(UPPER(p.CUSIP)) = TRIM(UPPER(m.{CUSIP_COL}))
     AND LTRIM(CAST(p.DWR_NO AS VARCHAR),'0') =
         LTRIM(CAST(m.DWR_NO AS VARCHAR),'0')
    WHERE CAST(m.{MSD_COL} AS FLOAT) != 0
      AND p.{PD_COL} IS NOT NULL AND m.{MSD_COL} IS NOT NULL
  """)

  Interpret median_ratio (only when ratio_stddev / median_ratio < 0.05):
    ≈ 1.0    → NO_SCALE_DIFFERENCE
    ≈ 0.01   → LEGACY_STORES_AS_PCT_INTEGER   (div by 100)
    ≈ 0.001  → LEGACY_STORES_AS_BASIS_POINTS  (div by 1000)
    ≈ 1000   → LEGACY_STORES_IN_THOUSANDS     (mult by 1000)
    ≈ 100    → MODERN_STORES_AS_PCT_INTEGER    (div modern by 100)
    noisy (stddev/median > 0.05) → SCALE_UNKNOWN, flag METHODOLOGY_DIFF

CODE VOCABULARY MAPPING:
  run_sql("""
    SELECT m.{MSD_COL} AS legacy_val, p.{PD_COL} AS modern_val, COUNT(*) AS freq
    FROM PRODUCT_DIM p
    JOIN MSD_CURRENT m
      ON TRIM(UPPER(p.CUSIP)) = TRIM(UPPER(m.{CUSIP_COL}))
     AND LTRIM(CAST(p.DWR_NO AS VARCHAR),'0') =
         LTRIM(CAST(m.DWR_NO AS VARCHAR),'0')
    WHERE m.{MSD_COL} IS NOT NULL AND p.{PD_COL} IS NOT NULL
    GROUP BY 1,2 ORDER BY 1, 3 DESC
  """)
  Build mapping table from co-occurrence.
  Clean 1:1 mapping → CODE_REMAP_DISCOVERED
  1:many → CODE_REMAP_AMBIGUOUS, flag NEEDS_SME

BOOLEAN DETECTION:
  Collect all distinct values from both sides.
  If values ⊆ {Y,N,YES,NO,T,F,TRUE,FALSE,1,0,' '} → BOOLEAN_NORMALIZATION

