## DIFFERENCE CLASSIFICATION
================================================================================

Apply the FIRST matching rule to every mismatch:

  Raw values identical, comparison failed due to type cast  → ENCODING_TYPE_CAST
  Normalized match after TRIM+UPPER only                    → ENCODING_WHITESPACE_CASE
  Normalized match after date format conversion             → ENCODING_DATE_FORMAT
  Normalized match after scale/magnitude correction         → ENCODING_NUMERIC_SCALE
  Normalized match after boolean normalization              → BOOLEAN_REPR
  Normalized match after sentinel→NULL substitution         → SENTINEL_VS_NULL
  Normalized match after discovered code remap              → CODE_REMAP_RESOLVED
  Normalized match after FIPS→state alpha                   → LOOKUP_REMAP
  Text fields match after abbreviation expansion            → ABBREVIATION
  Issuer or name field, tokens overlap significantly        → DESCRIPTION_VARIANCE
  Rating: tier matches, modifier differs                    → ENCODING_RATING_MODIFIER
  Rating: notation style differs, ordinal equivalent matches → RATING_NOTATION_REMAP
  Rating: watch or outlook differs only                     → RATING_QUALIFIER_DIFF
  Rating: agency notation in wrong field                    → AGENCY_FIELD_SWAP
  Rating: investment grade boundary crossed                 → RATING_IG_BOUNDARY_BREACH
  Rate diff < 0.001 after scale normalization               → ROUNDING_CONVENTION
  Date diff 1–3 days on non-contractual date fields         → BUSINESS_DAY_CONVENTION
  Date diff 1–3 days on MATURITY_DATE or DATED_DATE         → GENUINE_MISMATCH (Tier 1)
  Amount diff explainable by accrued interest formula       → ACCRUED_INTEREST_INCLUSION
  Amount diff is round percentage of authorized amount      → PARTIAL_ISSUANCE
  Scale ratio is unstable (stddev/median > 0.05)            → METHODOLOGY_DIFF
  No rule matches                                           → GENUINE_MISMATCH

