## PRIORITY TIERS
================================================================================

TIER 1 — BLOCKING (must resolve before migration sign-off)
  CUSIP format or length error in either system
  ONLY_IN_LEGACY coverage gap
  MATURITY_DATE any mismatch after full normalization
  COUPON_RATE diff > 0.001 after scale normalization
  PAR_AMOUNT diff > 0.1% after magnitude normalization
  TAX_STATUS mismatch
  BOND_TYPE mismatch
  AGENCY_FIELD_SWAP
  RATING_IG_BOUNDARY_BREACH
  SOURCE_DATA_INCONSISTENT on any critical financial field
  METHODOLOGY_DIFF on coupon, par, or yield

TIER 2 — NEEDS REVIEW (document and obtain SME approval)
  FIRST_CALL_DATE mismatch
  RATING tier mismatch within same grade band
  YIELD diff > 0.001 after scale normalization
  DAY_COUNT_CONVENTION mismatch on fixed-rate bonds
  PAYMENT_FREQUENCY mismatch
  IS_REFUNDED or IS_ESCROWED mismatch
  INSURER mismatch
  SENTINEL_VS_NULL on analytics fields
  PARTIAL_ISSUANCE
  ACCRUED_INTEREST_INCLUSION
  CODE_REMAP_AMBIGUOUS (1:many code mapping)

TIER 3 — ACCEPTABLE VARIANCE (document, no sign-off required)
  DESCRIPTION_VARIANCE on name fields
  SERIES_DESCRIPTION differences
  ENCODING_WHITESPACE_CASE
  ENCODING_DATE_FORMAT (normalized values match)
  ENCODING_RATING_MODIFIER
  RATING_QUALIFIER_DIFF (watch/outlook only)
  RATING_NOTATION_REMAP (resolved by notation map)
  BOOLEAN_REPR (normalized values match)
  ROUNDING_CONVENTION < 0.001
  BUSINESS_DAY_CONVENTION 1–3 days on non-contractual dates
  NEW_FIELD, DEPRECATED_FIELD
  LOOKUP_REMAP (FIPS resolved cleanly)
  CODE_REMAP_RESOLVED

================================================================================
## ESCALATION TRIGGERS
================================================================================

Flag NEEDS_SME and pause field comparison immediately if:

  Mismatch rate > 30% on any Tier 1 concept after all normalization
  METHODOLOGY_DIFF on yield, coupon, or par amount
  Any CUSIP in legacy not found in renovated system
  AGENCY_FIELD_SWAP detected (ratings in wrong columns)
  Scale ratio is noisy (ratio_stddev / median_ratio > 0.05)
  PAYMENT_FREQUENCY and DAY_COUNT_CONVENTION both mismatch on same bond
  MATURITY_DATE or DATED_DATE difference persists after all normalization
  DATE_FORMAT_UNKNOWN — no format exceeds 90% parse success
  CODE_REMAP_AMBIGUOUS — one legacy code maps to multiple modern values

================================================================================
## ERROR HANDLING
================================================================================

If run_sql() returns an error on a column:
  Log: { table, column, error_message, query_attempted }
  Skip that column pair only
  Continue with remaining columns
  Never halt the full run on a single column failure
  Report all skipped columns in MAPPING output under status = SQL_ERROR

